# Full-stack app (`apps/web` — planned). Copy to `.env` and fill from `supabase status`.
# Demo (`nx serve demo`) does not need these — it uses mock adapters.

# Supabase API URL:
# - CLI local stack (`npm run db:start`): http://127.0.0.1:54321
# - Existing docker-compose (Kong): http://127.0.0.1:8000 — see supabase/README.md
SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321

# Publishable key from `npm run db:status` (CLI 2.x; legacy name kept for app code)
# Also works: legacy anon JWT if your stack still shows one
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
